The Vice President spoke at the Apostolic Church of God in Chicago, Illinois, thanking Congressman Bobby Rush for his work and praising his leadership. She also congratulated Reverend Dr. Freddy Haynes on his new role and expressed gratitude to Reverend Jesse Jackson and his family for their continued leadership. The Vice President highlighted Reverend Jackson's work in building coalitions and expanding democracy, emphasizing the importance of unity and inclusivity. She shared personal experiences of working with Reverend Jackson and highlighted his impact on her career. The Vice President discussed the current challenges facing the nation, including attacks on voting rights, diversity, and women's reproductive rights. She urged the audience to stand together and fight for justice and equality, emphasizing the power of coalition-building. The Vice President concluded by invoking hope and encouraging continued activism.